Title : List of Mahaviharas of Newar Buddhism
Text : [[Newar Buddhism]] is one of the branches of [[Buddhism]]. One of the major elements of this branch of Buddhism is ''Mahavihara'' (महाबिहार) or ''Baha'' or great monastery. These monasteries have served as centers of learning in Newar Buddhism. These monasteries generally are built as a courtyard surrounded by two storied buildings consisting of halls.<ref name=Lalitpur>[http://www.lalitpur.org.np/e_historical_monuments.php Historical Monuments & World Heritage Sites, Lalitpur Sub-Metropolitan City]</ref> Some of these monasteries have been founded as early as fifth<ref name= Asiatravel/> to twelfth century <ref>[http://www.spinybabbler.org/art_complex/display_art_complexes.php?id=hiranya_varna_mahabihar.htm Hiranya Varna Mahabihar] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724132620/http://www.spinybabbler.org/art_complex/display_art_complexes.php?id=hiranya_varna_mahabihar.htm |date=2011-07-24 }}</ref> Many of these mahaviharas are listed as historical monuments of Nepal.<ref name=Lalitpur/> The following is a list of these mahaviharas <ref name=Lalitpur/><ref name= Asiatravel/><ref>[http://www.nepalmandal.com/content/13087.html Article:थथुप्वीं आचागुथिया छगू सन्दर्भ, Author: Anarratna Bajracharya, Language: Nepal Bhasa, Publication: Sandhya Times]</ref><ref>[http://www.lalitpur.org.np/n_historical_monuments.php Historical and World Heritage sites of Lalitpur (Nepali)]</ref> -
